<TITLE> Pintu's Monday bail frozen </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 4 (bdnews24.com)  The Supreme Court's Appellate Division has stayed for 10 days a High Court order that granted bail to former BNP MP Nasiruddin Ahmed Pintu in the BDR mutiny case on Monday. Appellate Division chamber judge, Justice Mohammed Muzammel Hossain gave the order on Tuesday following a government petition. Attorney general Mahbubey Alam and senior lawyer Anisul Haque argued for the government. Pintu secured bail on Monday from the High Court bench of justices Sheikh Rezwan Ali and Habibul Gani. He was arrested on June 2 last year at the High Court premises on charges of abetting BDR mutineers escape border force's Peelkhana headquarters during the mutiny last year. bd
